class mewbot.data.DataSource¶

Bases: Generic[DataType], ABC

A source of data for use in behaviours. A data source can contain any number of items with a common primitive type.

The source can be accessed as if it is an array, dictionary, or single value; each subclass must support one of these, but may support any combination thereof.

abstract get() → DataType¶

Returns an item in this Source. The source can choose if this is the first item, a random item, or the next in the iteration of this source (or any other semantics that make sense for the source). This function may raise an IOException if there is a problem communicating with the backing store for this source, or a DataSourceEmpty exception if there is no data to return.

abstract keys() → Sequence[str]¶

All the keys for a dictionary accessed source.

abstract random() → DataType¶

Gets a random item from this source.

mewbot.loader module¶

mewbot.loader.assert_message(obj: Any, interface: Type[Any]) → str¶

Generates the assert error message for an incomplete interface

mewbot.loader.configure_bot(name: str, stream: TextIO) → Bot¶

Loads a series of components from a YAML file to crate a bot

The YAML is expected to be a series of IOConfig, DataSource, and Behaviour blocks.

mewbot.loader.get_implementation(implementation: str) → Type[Any]¶

Gets a Class object from a module based on a fully-qualified name

This will attempt to load the module if it is not already loaded

mewbot.loader.load_behaviour(config: BehaviourConfigBlock) → BehaviourInterface¶

Creates a behaviour and its components based on a configuration block

mewbot.loader.load_component(config: ConfigBlock) → IOConfigInterface | TriggerInterface | ConditionInterface | ActionInterface | BehaviourInterface¶

Creates a component based on a configuration block
